S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: track - a rough path or way formed by use path - a way or track laid down for walking or made by continual treading.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: major street
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a main road, in an urban area, for through traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: minor street
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a secondary road, in an urban area, for local traffic.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of runway
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of runway based on primary aircraft type.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aeroplane Runway
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A level stretch of land where aeroplanes take off and land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Helicopter Landing Pad
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A site on which helicopters may land and take off.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: category of schedule
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the type of schedule, e.g., opening, closure, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: normal operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service, office, is open, fully manned, and operating normally, or the area is accessible as usual.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: closure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service, office, or area is closed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unmanned operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service is available but not manned.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of sea area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an area based on its physical characteristics

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: gat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a natural or artificial passage or channel through shoals or steep banks, or across a line of banks lying between two channels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bank
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an elevation over which the depth of water is relatively shallow, but normally sufficient for safe surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deep
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: in oceanography, an obsolete term which was generally restricted to depths greater than 6,000 m.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an indentation in the coastline.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trench
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long narrow, characteristically very deep and asymmetrical depression of the sea floor, with relatively steep sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: basin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a depression, characteristically in the deep sea floor, more or less equidimensional in plan and of variable extent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mud Flats
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A level tract of land, as the bed of a dry lake or an area frequently uncovered at low tide. Usually in plural.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: reef
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: rock lying at or near the sea surface that may constitute a hazard to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ledge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rocky formation continuous with and fringing the shore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: canyon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively narrow, deep depression with steep sides, the bottom of which generally has a continuous slope, developed characteristically on some continental slopes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: narrows
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a navigable narrow part of a bay, strait, river, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shoal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an offshore hazard to surface navigation that is composed of unconsolidated material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: knoll
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively small isolated elevation of a rounded shape.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (a) A long, narrow elevation with steep sides. (b) A long, narrow elevation often separating ocean basins. (c) The linked major mid-oceanic mountain systems of global extent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seamount
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large isolated elevation, greater than 1000m in relief above the sea floor, characteristically of conical form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pinnacle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any high tower or spire-shaped pillar or rock or coral, alone or cresting a summit. It may extend above the surface of the water. It may or may not be a hazard to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: abyssal plain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an extensive, flat, gently sloping or nearly level region at abyssal depths.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: plateau
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a flat or nearly flat area of considerable extent, dropping off abruptly on one or more sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spur
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a subordinate elevation, ridge or rise projecting outward from a larger feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shelf
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a zone adjacent to a continent (or around an island) and extending from the low water line to a depth at which there is usually a marked increase of slope towards oceanic depths.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trough
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long depression of the sea floor characteristically flat bottomed and steep sided and normally shallower than a trench.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: saddle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a broad pass, resembling in shape a riding saddle, in a ridge or between contiguous seamounts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: abyssal hills
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tract, on occasion extensive, of low (100-500m) elevations on the deep sea floor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: apron
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a gently dipping featureless surface, underlain primarily by sediment, at the base of any steeper slope.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: archipelagic apron
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a gentle slope with a generally smooth surface on the sea floor, characteristically found around groups of islands or seamounts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: borderland
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a region adjacent to a continent, normally occupied by or bordering a shelf, that is highly irregular with depths well in excess of those typical of a shelf.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: continental margin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the zone, generally consisting of shelf, slope and rise, separating the continent from the abyssal plain or deep sea floor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: continental rise
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a gentle slope rising from the oceanic depths towards the foot of a continental slope.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: escarpment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an elongated and comparatively steep slope separating or gently sloping areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fan
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively smooth, fan-like, depositional feature normally sloping away from the outer termination of a canyon or canyon system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fracture zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an extensive linear zone of irregular topography of the sea floor, characterized by steep-sided or asymmetrical ridges, troughs or escarpments.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: gap
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a narrow break in a ridge or a rise.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: guyot
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a seamount having a comparatively smooth flat top.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a small isolated elevation (see also abyssal hills).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hole
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a local depression, often steep sided, of the sea floor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: levee
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a depositional embankment bordering a canyon, valley or deep-sea channel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: median valley
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the axial depression of the mid-oceanic ridge system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: moat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an annular depression that may not be continuous, located at the base of many seamounts, islands and other isolated elevations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mountains
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large and complex grouping of ridges and seamounts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: peak
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a prominent elevation either pointed or of a very limited extent across the summit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: province
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a region identifiable by a group of similar physiographic features whose characteristics are markedly in contrast with surrounding areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rise
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (a) A broad elevation that rises gently and generally smoothly from the sea floor. (b) The linked major mid-oceanic mountain systems of global extent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sea channel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a continuously sloping, elongated narrow depression commonly found in fans or abyssal plains and customarily bordered by levees on one or both sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seamount Chain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Several seamounts in linear or arcuate alignment. Also called: seamounts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shelf-edge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a narrow zone at the seaward margin of a shelf along which is a marked increase of slope.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a sea floor barrier of relatively shallow depth restricting water movement between basins.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: slope
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the slope seaward from the shelf edge to the upper edge of a continental rise or the point where there is a general reduction in slope.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: terrace
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively flat horizontal or gently inclined surface, sometimes long and narrow, which is bounded by a steeper ascending slope on one side and by a steeper descending slope on the opposite side.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: valley
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively shallow, wide depression, the bottom of which usually has a continuous gradient. This term is generally not used for features that have canyon-like characteristics for a significant portion of their extent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: canal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an artificial water course used for navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lake
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large body of water entirely surrounded by land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: river
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively large natural stream of water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: reach
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a straight section of a river, especially a navigable river between two bends or an arm of the sea extending into the land

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Intertidal Cay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A low, flat island of sand, coral, etc. awash or submerged at high water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Submarine volcano
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a vent in the earth's crust through which lava, steam, ashes, etc., are expelled, either continuously or at irregular intervals that is located underwater

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of shoreline construction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of shoreline construction based on use

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: breakwater
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure protecting a shore area, harbour, anchorage, or basin from waves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: groyne (groin)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a low artificial wall-like structure of durable material extending from the land to seaward for a particular purpose, such as to prevent coast erosion

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mole
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a form of breakwater alongside which vessels may lie on the sheltered side only in some cases it may lie entirely within an artificial harbour, permitting vessels to lie along both sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pier (jetty)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long, narrow structure extending into the water to afford a berthing place for vessels, to serve as a promenade, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: promenade pier
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pier built only for recreational purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wharf (quay)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure serving as a berthing place for vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: training wall
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wall or bank, often submerged, built to direct or confine the flow of a river or tidal current, or to promote a scour action.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rip rap
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A layer of broken rock, cobbles, boulders, or fragments of sufficient size to resist the erosive forces of flowing water and wave action.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: revetment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: facing of stone or other material, either permanent or temporary, placed along the edge of a stream, river or canal to stabilize the bank and to protect it from the erosive action of the stream.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sea wall
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an embankment or wall for protection against waves or tidal action along a shore or water front.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: landing steps
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: steps at the shoreline as the connection between land and water on different levels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ramp
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a sloping structure that can either be used, as a landing place, at variable water levels, for small vessels, landing ships, or a ferry boat, or for hauling a cradle carrying a vessel, which may include rails.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: slipway
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the prepared and usually reinforced inclined surface on which keel- and bilge-blocks are laid for supporting a vessel under construction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fender
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a protective structure designed to cushion the impact of a vessel and prevent damage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: solid face wharf
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wharf consisting of a solid wall of concrete, masonry, wood etc., such that the water cannot circulate freely under the wharf. The type of construction affects ship-handling for example, a solid face wharf may give shelter from tidal streams, but under certain circumstances a cusion of water may build up between such a wharf and a ship attempting to berth at it, causing difficulties in ship handling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: open face wharf
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wharf supported on piles or other structures which allow free circulation of water under the wharf.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: log ramp
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an inclined plane used to dump logs into the water for transport, or to haul logs out of the water for processing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swimming facility
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An artificial pool or swimming enclosure, especially one in the open air, which may beconstructed of wire mesh or heavy netting supported by cables, buoys or piles, for swimming in.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of signal station, traffic
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of station based on the traffic service provided

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: port control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels within a port.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: port entry and departure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels entering or leaving a port.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Port Traffic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station displaying International Port Traffic signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: berthing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels when berthing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels entering or leaving a dock.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels entering or leaving a lock.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flood barrage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels wishing to pass through a flood control barrage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bridge passage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station for the control of vessels wishing to pass under a bridge.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dredging
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal station indicating when dredging is in progress.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: traffic control light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: visual signal lights placed in a waterway to indicate to shipping the movements authorised at the time at which they are shown.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of signal station, warning
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of station based on the warning service provided

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: danger
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message warning of the presence of a danger to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: maritime obstruction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message warning of the presence of a maritime obstruction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message warning of the presence of a cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: military practice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message warning of activity in a military practice area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: distress
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a station that may receive or transmit distress signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: weather
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a visual signal displayed to indicate a weather forecast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: storm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message conveying information about storm conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message conveying information about ice conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: time
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an accurate signal marking a specified time or time interval. It is used primarily for determining errors of timepieces. Such signals are usually sent from an observatory by radio or telegraph, but visual signals are used at some ports.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message conveying information on tidal conditions in the area in question.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tidal stream
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message conveying information on condition of tidal currents in the area in question.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tide gauge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a device for measuring the height of tide. A graduated staff in a sheltered area where visual observations can be made or it may consist of an elaborate recording instrument making a continuous graphic record of tide height against time. Such an instrument is usually actuated by a float in a pipe communicating with the sea through a small hole which filters out shorter waves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tide scale
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a visual scale which directly shows the height of the water above chart datum or a local datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diving
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal or message warning of diving activity

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: water level gauge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a device for measuring and conveying information about the water level (non-tidal) in the area in question.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of silo/tank
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification based on the product for which a silo or tank is used.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: silo in general
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a generally cylindrical tower used for storing fodder or grain.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tank in general
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a fixed structure for storing liquids.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: grain elevator
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a storage building for grain. Usually a tall frame, metal or concrete structure with an especially compartmented interior.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: water tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tower with an elevated container used to hold water.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of slope
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a stretch of ground forming a natural or artificial incline

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cutting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an excavation through high ground for a road, canal, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: embankment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an artificial elevation constructed from earth, stone, etc. carrying a road, railway or similar or serving to dam water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dune
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mound, ridge or hill of drifted material on the sea coast or in a desert.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a small isolated elevation, smaller than a mountain.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pingo
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a dome-shaped hill formed in a permafrost area when the hydrostatic pressure of freezing ground water causes the upheaval of a layer of frozen ground.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cliff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: land rising abruptly for a considerable distance above the water or surrounding land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: scree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: rocky debris on the side or at the foot of a mountain forming a steep stony slope.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of small craft facility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of services and facilities for the small craft user

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visitor's berth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a berth set aside for the use of visiting vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nautical club
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a club for mariners generally associated with other small craft facilities.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boat hoist
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a hoist for lifting boats out of the water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sailmaker
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where sails are made or may be taken for repair.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boatyard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place on shore where boats may be built, stored and repaired.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: public inn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a public house providing food, drink and accommodation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: restaurant
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a commercial establishment serving food.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: chandler
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a dealer in ships' supplies.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: provisions
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where food and other such supplies are available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: doctor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where a doctor is available to provide medical attention.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pharmacy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where medical drugs are dispensed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: water tap
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where fresh water is available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fuel station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where fuel is available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: electricity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where a connection to an electrical supply is available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bottle gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where bottled gas is available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: showers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where showers are available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: launderette
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where there are facilities for washing clothes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: public toilets
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where toilets are available for public use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: post box
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where mail may be posted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: public telephone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where a telephone is available for public use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: refuse bin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where refuse may be dumped.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: car park
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where cars may be parked.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: parking for boats and trailers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place on shore where boats and/or trailers may be parked.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: caravan site
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where caravans may be parked or where caravan accommodation is provided.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: camping site
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where visitors may pitch tents and camp.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sewerage pump-out station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where sewerage may be pumped off a vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: emergency telephone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where a telephone is available for emergency use only.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: landing/launching place for boats
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where boats may be landed or launched.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visitors mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mooring set aside for the use of visiting vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: scrubbing berth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where vessels may berth for the purpose of careening.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: picnic area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where people may go to eat a picnic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mechanics workshop
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where mechanical repairs can be undertaken to engines or other vessel equipment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: guard and/or security service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where a vessel is patrolled by a security service or stored in a secure lockup.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of special purpose mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an aid to navigation which signifies some special purpose
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A mark may be a beacon, a buoy, a signpost or may take another form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: firing danger mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate a firing danger area, usually at sea.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: target mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any object toward which something is directed. The distinctive marking or instrumentation of a ground point to aid its identification on a photograph.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: marker ship mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark marking the position of a ship which is used as a target during some military exercise.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: degaussing range mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate a degaussing range.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: barge mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark of relevance to barges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cable mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate the position of submarine cables or the point at which they run on to the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spoil ground mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate the limit of a spoil ground

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: outfall mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate the position of an outfall or the point at which it leaves the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ODAS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Ocean Data Acquisition System

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: recording mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to record data for scientific purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seaplane anchorage mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate a seaplane anchorage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: recreation zone mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate a recreation zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mooring mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating a mooring or moorings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: LANBY
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large buoy designed to take the place of a lightship where construction of an offshore light station is not feasible.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: leading mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: aids to navigation or other indicators so located as to indicate the path to be followed. Leading marks identify a leading line when they are in transit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: measured distance mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark forming part of a transit indicating one end of a measured distance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: notice mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a notice board or sign indicating information to the mariner.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: TSS mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating a traffic separation scheme.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: anchoring prohibited mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating an anchoring prohibited area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: berthing prohibited mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that berthing is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: overtaking prohibited mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that overtaking is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: two-way traffic prohibited mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating a one-way route.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 'reduced wake' mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that vessels must not generate excessive wake.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: speed limit mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that a speed limit applies.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stop mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the place where the bow of a ship must stop when traffic lights show red.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: general warning mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that special caution must be exercised in the vicinity of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 'Sound Ship's Siren' Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a ship should sound its siren or horn.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: restricted vertical clearance mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the minimum vertical space available for passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: maximum vessel's draught mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the maximum draught of vessel permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: restricted horizontal clearance mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the minimum horizontal space available for passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: strong current warning mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark warning of strong currents.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: berthing permitted mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that berthing is allowed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: overhead power cable mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating an overhead power cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 'channel edge gradient' mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the gradient of the slope of a dredge channel edge.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: telephone mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the presence of a telephone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ferry crossing mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that a ferry route crosses the ship route often used with a 'sound ship's siren' mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pipeline mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate the position of submarine pipelines or the point at which they run on to the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: anchorage mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating an anchorage area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: clearing mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark used to indicate a clearing line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: control mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the location at which a restriction or requirement exists.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diving mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that diving may take place in the vicinity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: refuge beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark providing or indicating a place of safety.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: foul ground mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating a foul ground.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: yachting mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark installed for use by yachtsmen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: heliport mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating an area where helicopters may land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GNSS Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a location at which a GNSS position has been accurately determined.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seaplane landing mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating an area where sea-planes land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: entry prohibited mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that entry is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: work in progress mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating that work (generally construction) is in progress.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mark with unknown purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark whose detailed characteristics are unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wellhead mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating a borehole that produces or is capable of producing oil or natural gas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: channel separation mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the point at which a channel divides separately into two channels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: marine farm mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the existence of a fish, mussel, oyster or pearl farm/ culture.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: artificial reef mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mark indicating the existence or the extent of an artificial reef.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark, used year round, that may be submerged when ice passes through the area

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nature reserve mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to define the boundary of a nature reserve.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Aggregating Device (FAD)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A fish aggregating (or aggregation) device (FAD) is a man-made object used to attract ocean going pelagic fish such as marlin, tuna and mahi-mahi (dolphin fish). They usually consist of buoys or floats tethered to the ocean floor with concrete blocks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wreck mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a wreck

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a customs checkpoint.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Causeway mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a causeway.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wave Recorder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A surface following buoy used to measure wave activity.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Temporal Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An assessment of the likelihood of change over time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extreme event
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indication of the possible impact of a significant event (for example hurricane, earthquake, volcanic eruption, landslide, etc), which is considered likely to have changed the seafloor or landscape significantly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change and Significant Shoaling Expected
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example river siltation, sand waves, seasonal storms, ice bergs, etc) that is likely to result in new significant shoaling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change But Significant Shoaling Not Expected
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example sand wave shift, seasonal storms, ice bergs, etc) that is not likely to result in new significant shoaling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change to non-bathymetric features (for example river siltation, glacier creep/recession, sand dunes, buoys, marine farms, etc).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unlikely to Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Significant change to the seafloor is not expected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unassessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Temporal variation not assessed or cannot be determined.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Tidal stream
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the alternating horizontal movement of water associated with the rise and fall of the tide caused by tide producing forces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flood stream
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the horizontal movement of water associated with the rising tide.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ebb stream
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the horizontal movement of water associated with falling tide.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other tidal flow
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any other horizontal movement of water associated with tides, e.g., rotary flow.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Traffic Separation Scheme
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International classification of traffic separation scheme

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IMO - Adopted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A defined Traffic Separation Scheme that has been adopted as an IMO routing measure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: not IMO - adopted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a defined Traffic Separation Scheme that has not been adopted as an IMO routing measure.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of vegetation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the plant life of an area or region

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bush
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shrub or clump of shrubs with stems of moderate length.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deciduous wood
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wood with trees that shed their leaves annually.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coniferous wood
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wood with evergreen trees of a group usually bearing cones, including yews, cedars and redwoods.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wood in general (inc mixed wood)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Growing trees densely occupying a tract of land

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mangroves
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: one of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low lying coasts into shallow water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tree in general
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a woody perennial plant, having a self supporting main stem or trunk.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: evergreen tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tree which keeps its foliage all year round.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coniferous tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cone-bearing, needle-leaved or scale-leaved evergreen tree.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: palm tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tropical or sub-tropical tree, shrub or vine having a tall, unbranched, columnar trunk. The trunk is crowned by a tuft or large, pleated fan or feather shaped leaves with stout sheathing and often prickly petioles (stalks), the persistent bases of which frequently clothe the trunk.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nipa palm tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rare palm tree with regular branching involving equal or sub-equal division of the apex that results in forking.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: casuarina tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tree characterized by slender, green, often drooping branches that are deeply grooved and that bear, at intervals, whorls of tine leaves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: eucalypt tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an instance of a large genus of mostly very large trees (90 metres).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deciduous tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tree which sheds its foliage for part of the year (generally in winter).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mangrove tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: one of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low lying coasts in to shallow waters.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: filao tree
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a variety of tropical or sub-tropical tree.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of water turbulence
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an unstable sea state

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: breakers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: waves breaking on the shore, over a reef, etc. Breakers may be roughly classified into three kinds, although the categories may overlap: spilling breakers break gradually over a considerable distance plunging breakers tend to curl over and break with a crash and surging breakers peak up, but then instead of spilling or plunging they surge up on the beach face. The French word 'brisant' is also used for the obstacle causing the breaking of the wave.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: eddies
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: circular movements of water usually formed where currents pass obstructions, between two adjacent currents flowing counter to each other, or along the edge of a permanent current.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: overfalls
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: short, breaking waves occurring when a strong current passes over a shoal or other submarine obstruction or meets a contrary current or wind.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tide rips
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: small waves formed on the surface of water by the meeting of opposing tidal currents or by a tidal current crossing an irregular bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bombora
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wave that forms over a submerged offshore reef or rock, sometimes (in very calm weather or at high tide) nearly swelling but in other conditions breaking heavily and producing a dangerous stretch of broken water the reef or rock itself.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of weed/kelp
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of marine vegetation

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: kelp
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a giant plant sometimes 60 metres long with no roots, it is anchored by hold-fasts or tendrils up to 10 metres long, that cling to rock. Gas filled bubbles on fronds act as floats keeping the kelp just below the surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seaweed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: general name for marine plants of the algae class which grow in long narrow ribbons.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seagrass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any grasslike marine alga. Eelgrass is one of the best known seagrasses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sargasso
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a certain type of sea weed, or more generally, a large floating mass of this sea weed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of wreck
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a wrecked or ruined ship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: non-dangerous wreck
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wreck which is not considered to be dangerous to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dangerous wreck
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wreck which is considered to be dangerous to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: distributed remains of wreck
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (foul ground) an area over which it is safe to navigate but which should be avoided for anchoring, taking the ground or ground fishing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wreck showing mast/masts
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: wreck of which only the mast(s) is visible at the sounding datum indicated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wreck showing any portion of hull or superstructure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: wreck of which any portion of the hull or superstructure is visible at the sounding datum indicated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The property possessed by an object of producing different sensations on the eye as a result of the way it reflects or emits light.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour pattern
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A regular repeated design containing more than one colour

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: horizontal stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: straight bands or stripes of differing colours painted horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: vertical stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: straight bands or stripes of differing colours painted vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diagonal stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: straight bands or stripes of differing colours painted diagonally (ie not horizontally or vertically).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: squared
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: often referred to as checker plate, where alternate colours are used to create squares similar to a chess or draught board. The pattern may be straight or diagonal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stripes (direction unknown)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: straight bands or stripes of differing colours painted in an unknown direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: border stripe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a band or stripe of colour which is displayed around the outer edge of the object, which may also form a border to an inner pattern or plain colour.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Communication channel
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A channel number assigned to a specific radio frequency, frequencies or frequency band.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The expected input is the specific VHF-Channel. The attribute 'communication channel' encodes the various VHF-channels used for communication.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Condition
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various conditions of buildings and other constructions.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The default 'condition' should be considered to be completed, undamaged and working normally. This attribute should, therefore, only be used to indicate objects whose condition is anything other than 'normal'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: under construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure that is in the process of being built.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ruined
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure in a decayed or deteriorated condition resulting from neglect or disuse, or a damaged structure in need of repair.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: under reclamation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of the sea that is being reclaimed as land, usually by the dumping of earth and other material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wingless
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a windmill or windmotor from which the turbine blades are missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: planned construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area where a future construction is planned.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: contact instructions
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Instructions provided on how to contact a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Data assessment
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The categorisation of the assessment level of bathymetric data for anarea.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: assessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quality of the bathymetric data has been assessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Assessed (Oceanic)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quality of oceanic bathymetric data (depths deeper than 200 metres) has been assessed, however details are not required.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unassessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not having been assessed

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Disused
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that an entity ceases to be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004.? Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date of an event.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004.? Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date variable
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A day which is not fixed in the Gregorian calendar.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Examples: The fourth Thursday in November; new moon day of Kartika (Diwali); Easter Sunday.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Any one of seven days in a week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Monday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The second day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tuesday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The third day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wednesday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fourth day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Thursday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fifth day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Friday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The sixth day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Saturday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The seventh day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sunday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The first day of the week.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Day of week is range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if the days of the week identified define a range or not.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A True value is an indication that the identified days of the week define a range between and inclusive of those days.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Default Clearance Depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth value determined for an underwater hazard of unknown depth, based on the depth of the surrounding area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth range maximum value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum (deepest) value of a depth range.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative. The unit of measure is defined in the DUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the DUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 fm or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth range minimum value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum (shoalest) value of a depth range.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative. The unit of measure is defined in the DUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the DUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 fm or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Destination
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The place or general direction to which a vessel is going or directed.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: In addition to a placename of a port, harbour area or terminal, the place could include generalities such as "The north-west", or "upriver".

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Display Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a feature name is to be displayed in certain systemdisplay settings or not.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where it is allowable to encode multiple instances of feature name for a single feature instance, only onefeature name instance can indicate that the name is to be displayed (display name set to True).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Distance Unit of Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A specified amount of a quantity, as of length, by comparison with which any other quantity of the same kind is measured or estimated

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fundamental unit of length in the metric system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yards
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a common unit of linear measure in English-speaking countries, equal to 3 feet or 36 inches, and equivalent to 0.9144 meter

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Kilometres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of length, the common measure of distances equal to 1000 metres, and equivalent to 3280.8 feet or 0.621 mile.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Statute miles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The legal name for a mile

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautical miles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a unit of distance used chiefly in navigation, equal to 6080.20 feet (1853.25 meters) in the U.S., now replaced by the international nautical mile.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Dredged Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that dredging occurred.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Dredged date indicates the latest date of dredging (which may be the latest known date if the dredged area is not maintained), or the date of the latest control survey confirming the depth in a maintained dredged area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Elevation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The altitude of the ground level of an object, measured from a specified vertical datum.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Estimated Range of Transmission
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The estimated range of a non-optical electromagnetic transmission.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The estimated range (distance) assumes 'in vacuo' transmission and a standard antenna height of 5 metres. Thus it gives a hint to the mariner whether they are likely to receive transmission at a certain distance from an object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Exhibition condition of light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The outward display of the light

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: light shown without change of character
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light shown throughout the 24 hours without change of character.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: daytime light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light which is only exhibited by day.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fog light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light which is exhibited in fog or conditions of reduced visibility.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: night light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light which is only exhibited at night.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Exposition of sounding
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates objects with a 'value of sounding' not within the range of depth of the surrounding depth area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: These objects could be a potential danger for navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: within the range of depth of the surrounding depth area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth corresponds to the depth range of the surrounding depth area. i.e. the depth is not shoaler than the minimum depth of the surrounding depth area or deeper than the maximum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shoaler than the range of depth of the surrounding depth area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth is shoaler than the minimum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deeper than the range of depth of the surrounding depth area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth is deeper than the maximum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Flare angle
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angle about which the light flare symbol is rotated to be displayed in ECDIS.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The flare angle is calculated by ENC production software systems.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Flare Stack
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing whether an offshore platform has a stack used forburning-off waste oil or gas or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Flip bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The bearing at which text is re-located to the opposite side of a feature when screen display is oriented away from true north.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: frequency shore station receives
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shore station receiver frequency expressed in kHz to one decimal place.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Examples:4379.1 kHz becomes 04379113162.8 kHz becomes 131628

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: frequency shore station transmits
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shore station transmitter frequency expressed in kHz to one decimal place.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Examples: 4379.1 kHz becomes 043791 13162.8 kHz becomes 131628

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Full seafloor coverage achieved
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Expression stating if full seafloor coverage has been achieved in the area covered by hydrographic surveys.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: full seafloor coverage achieved applies to both the spatial completeness of feature detection and to the spatial completeness of the measurement of the regular seafloor. The former is further specified by the complex attribute features detected, the latter by the attributes depth range maximum value and depth range minimum value

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Function
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A specific role that describes a feature

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Harbour-Masters Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Local official who has charge of mooring and berthing of vessels, collecting harbour fees, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Serves as a government office where customs duties are collected, the flow of goods are regulated and restrictions enforced, and shipments or vehicles are cleared for entering or leaving a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: health office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the office which is charged with the administration of health laws and sanitary inspections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hospital
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an institution or establishment providing medical or surgical treatment for the ill or wounded.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: post office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the public department, agency or organisation responsible primarily for the collection, transmission and distribution of mail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hotel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an establishment, especially of a comfortable or luxurious kind, where paying visitors are provided with accommodation, meals and other services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: railway station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building with platforms where trains arrive, load, discharge and depart.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: police station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the office of the local police force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: water-police station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the headquarters of a local water-police force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pilot office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the office or headquarters of pilots the place where the services of a pilot may be obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pilot lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a distinctive structure on shore from which personnel keep watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bank office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an office for custody, deposit, loan, exchange or issue of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: headquarters for district control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the quarters of an executive officer (director, manager, etc.) with responsibility for an administrative area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: transit shed/warehouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building or part of a building for storage of wares or goods.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: factory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building or buildings with equipment for manufacturing a workshop.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: power station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a stationary plant containing apparatus for large scale conversion of some form of energy (such as hydraulic, steam, chemical or nuclear energy) into electrical energy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: administrative
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building for the management of affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: educational facility
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building concerned with education (e.g. school, college, university, etc.)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: church
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building for public Christian worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: chapel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place for Christian worship other than a parish, cathedral or church, especially one attached to a private house or institution.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building for public Jewish worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pagoda
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a Hindu or Buddhist temple or sacred building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shinto shrine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building for public Shinto worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: buddhist temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: see pagoda.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mosque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a Muslim place of worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: marabout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shrine marking the burial place of a Muslim holy man.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: keeping a watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: communication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: transmitting and/or receiving electronic communication signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: television
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: broadcast of television signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radio
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: broadcast of radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a method, system or technique of using beamed, reflected, and timed radio waves for detecting, locating, or tracking objects, and for measuring altitudes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: light support
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: supporting a light

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: microwave
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: broadcasting and receiving signals using microwaves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cooling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: dissipating heat.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: observation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place from which the surroundings can be observed but at which a watch is not habitually maintained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timeball
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A visual time signal in the form of a ball.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: clock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: visual time signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: used to control the flow of air, rail, or marine traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: airship mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a facility to secure an airship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stadium
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large usually unroofed building with tiers of seats for spectators

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bus station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a location at which buses arrive and from which they depart.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea rescue control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit responsible for promoting efficient organization of search and rescue services and for coordinating the conduct of search and rescue operations within a search and rescue region.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building designed and equipped for making observations of astronomical, meteorological, or other natural phenomena.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore crusher
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or structure used to crush ore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boathouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building or shed, usually built partly over water, for sheltering a boat or boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pumping Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A facility to move solids, liquids or gases by means of pressure or suction

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the object, measured from a specified vertical datum.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Height must not be used for floating objects. The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length of a feature, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical length of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal clearance value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The width of an object, such as a canal or a tunnel, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical width of the object.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The width of an object, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical width of the object

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal distance uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the horizontal accuracy of horizontal clearances and distances.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The error is assumed to be positive and negative. The plus/minus character must not be encoded.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the longer of two linear axis.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the shorter of two linear axis.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Ice factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the maximum variation in the vertical clearance of an overhead cable due to an accumulation of ice.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: In Dispute
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if an area is in a jurisdictional dispute.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: In the water
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication if the feature is located in or over navigable water.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A True value is an indication that the feature is to be included in the ECDIS Base Display viewing group.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Is MRCC
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if a coastguard station performs the function of a Maritime Rescue and Coordination Centre.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A True value is an indication that an encoded coastguard station performs the function of a Maritime Rescue and Coordination Centre.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Jurisdiction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The jurisdiction applicable to an administrative area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: international
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: involving more than one country covering more than one national area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: national
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area administered or controlled by a single nation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: national sub-division
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area smaller than the nation in which it lies.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The language is encoded by a 3 character code following ISO 639-2/T.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Least Depth of detected features measured
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Expression stating if the least depth ofdetected features in an area was measured.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: -A feature in this context is any object, whether manmade or not, projecting above the sea floor, which may be a danger for surface navigation (reference: IHO publication S-44).- least depth of detected features measured does not describe the least depth of features that were actually detected during a hydrographic survey, but the ability of the survey to detect the least depth of features with a maximum uncertainty as defined in IHO publication S-44.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Lifting capacity
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific safe lifting capacity of an object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Light characteristic
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The typical behaviour associated with the light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A selection of the above characteristics is defined and illustrated diagrammatically in IHO Chart Specifications, M-4, 471.2.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fixed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, with constant luminous intensity and colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: long-flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a flashing light in which a single flash of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: quick-flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light exhibiting without interruption very rapid regular alternations of light and darkness.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 80 flashes per minute but less than 160 flashes per minute. It may be:- Continuous very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated.- Group very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Continuous Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are regularly repeated at a rate of not less than 160 flashes per minute.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: isophased
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light with all durations of light and darkness equal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: occulting
