S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and all the eclipses are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Interrupted Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in which the ultra quick flashes (160 or more per minute) are interrupted at regular intervals by eclipses of long duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: morse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rhythmic light in which appearances of light of two clearly different durations are grouped to represent a character or characters in the Morse code.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a flashing light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which an occulting light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating light in which the total duration of light in each period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and in which the intervals of darkness (occultations) are all of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of very quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ultra Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of ultra quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal light that shows, in any given direction, two or more colours in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Alternating Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity and different colour.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Light visibility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific visibility of a light, with respect to the light's intensity and ease of recognition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: high intensity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: non-marine lights with a higher power than marine lights and visible from well off shore (often 'Aero' lights).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: low intensity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: non-marine lights with lower power than marine lights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: faint
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a decrease in the apparent intensity of a light which may occur in the case of partial obstructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: intensified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light in a sector is intensified (i.e. has longer range than other sectors).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unintensified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light in a sector is unintensified (i.e. has shorter range than other sectors).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visibility deliberately restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light sector is deliberately reduced in intensity, for example to reduce its effect on a built-up area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: said of the arc of a light sector designated by its limiting bearings in which the light is not visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: partially obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: this value specifies that parts of the sector are obscured.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visible in line of range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lights that must in line to be visible

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Line spacing maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum distance between hydrographic survey lines.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Line spacing minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum distance between hydrographic survey lines.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: linkage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Location (address) for on-line access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Magnetic Anomaly Value Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum value of the deviation from the normal magnetic variation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The deviation is assumed to be positive and negative. The plus/minus character must not be encoded.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Magnetic anomaly value minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: negative value of the deviation from the normalmagnetic variation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The deviation is assumed to be negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Major light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a light is considered to be a major light in terms ofECDIS display in a particular area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The attribute major light is only intended to provide an indication to the ECDIS that the light is consideredto be an important light in terms of its display. As such this is a cartographic attribute to aid the compiler indetermining the most appropriate display for a light; it is not intended to be used as a formal classificationmethod for lights.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marks navigational - System of
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: no system
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: CEVNI
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: CEVNI (European Code for Navigation on Inland Waterways) is the European code for rivers, canals land lakes in most of Europe.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The largest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum permitted draught
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum draught of a vessel permitted along a route, ina channel or dock, at a berth, or over a submerged feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Measured distance
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An accurately defined distance along a course at sea.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Measurement Distance Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum spacing of the principal measurement lines of a hydrographic survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Measurement Distance Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum spacing of the principal measurement lines of a hydrographic survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum display scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: MMSI Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The Maritime Mobile Service Identity (MMSI) Code is formed of a series of ninedigits which are transmitted over the radio path in order to uniquely identify ship stations, ship earth stations,coast stations, coast earth stations, and group calls. These identities are formed in such a way that theidentity or part thereof can be used by telephone and telex subscribers connected to the generaltelecommunications network principally to call ships automatically. (Adapted from Appendix 43 of theInternational Telecommunications Union Radio Regulations).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Moire effect
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A short range (up to 2km) type of directional light. Sodium lighting gives ayellow background to a screen on which a vertical black line will be seen by an observer on the centre line.(S-57 Edition 3.1, Appendix A ? Chapter 2, Page 2.49, November 2000).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Multiplicity known
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-locatedgroup is or is not known. (Adapted from S-57 Edition 3.1, Appendix A ? Chapter 2, Page 2.150, November2000).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: name of resource
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the online resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nationality
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier of membership of a particular nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of construction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The buildings primary construction material

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Masonry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of stones or bricks, usually quarried, shaped, and mortared.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: concreted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: constructed of concrete, a material made of sand and gravel that is united by cement into a hardened mass used for roads, foundations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: loose boulders
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: constructed from large stones or blocks of concrete, often placed loosely for protection against waves or water turbulence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hard Surfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with a surface of hard material, usually a term applied to roads surfaced with asphalt or concrete.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unsurfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: constructed with no extra protection, usually a term applied to roads not surfaced with a hard material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wooden
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: constructed from wood.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: constructed from metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: glass reinforced plastic (GRP)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: constructed from a plastic material strengthened with fibres of glass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Latticed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure of crossed wooden or metal strips usually arranged to form a diagonal pattern of open spaces between the strips.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 1. any artificial or natural substance having similar properties and composition, as fused borax, obsidian, or the like.2. something made of such a substance, as a windowpane.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of surface
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The general material which the land surface or the sea bed is composed.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Mixed bottom: where the seabed comprises a mixture of material, the main constituent is given first e.g., fine sand with mud and shells would be indicated as 4,1,17. Mud, sand, stone, rock are terms used for the general description. Clay, silt, gravel, pebbles, cobbles are more specific terms related to particle size.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mud
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: soft, wet earth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (particles of less than 0.002mm) stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: silt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (particles of 0.002-0.0625mm) when dried on hand will rub off easily.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: gravel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (particles of 2.0-4.0mm) small stones with coarse sand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pebbles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small stone worn smooth and rounded by the action of water, sand, ice, etc. ranging in diameter between 4 and 64 millimetres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cobbles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (particles of 64.0-256.0mm) stones worn round and smooth by water and used for paving.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any formation of natural origin that constitutes an integral part of the lithosphere. The natural occurring material that forms firm, hard, and solid masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lava
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the fluid or semi-fluid matter flowing from a volcano. The substance that results from the cooling of the molten rock. Part of the ocean bed is composed of lava.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hard calcareous skeletons of many tribes of marine polyps.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shells
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Exoskeletons of various water dwelling animals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boulder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rounded rock with diameter of 256 mm or larger.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of surface - qualifying terms
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The nature of various forms of natural surface materials in terms of their size, morphology and consistency.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: falls within the smallest size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: medium
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: falls within the moderate size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coarse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: falls within the largest size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: broken
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: fractured or in pieces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sticky
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: having an adhesive or glue like property.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: soft
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: not hard or firm.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stiff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: not pliant thick, resistant to flow.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: volcanic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: composed of or containing material ejected from a volcano.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: calcareous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: composed of or containing calcium or calcium carbonate.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: firm usually refers to an area of the sea floor not covered by unconsolidated sediment.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Number of features
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-locatedgroup.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a bearing.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pictorial representation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A reference to a pictorial representation of the feature.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The 'pictorial representation' could be a drawing or a photo. The string encodes the file name of an external graphic file (pixel/vector).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pilot movement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of pilot activity by arrival, departure, or change of pilot. It may also describe the place where the pilot's advice begins, ends, or is transferred to a different pilot.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: embarkation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The place where vessels not being navigated according to a pilot's instructions pick up a pilot while in transit from sea to a port or constricted waters for future navigation under pilot instructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: disembarkation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The place where vessels being navigated under a pilot's instructions in transit from sea to a port or constricted waters drop the pilot and proceed without being subject to pilot instructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pilot change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The place where vessels being navigated under a pilot's instructions drop off the pilot and pick up a different pilot for future navigation under pilot's instructions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Product
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various substances which are transported, stored or exploited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: oil
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a thick, slippery liquid that will not dissolve in water, usually petroleum based in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a substance with particles that can move freely, usually a fuel substance in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a colourless, odourless, tasteless liquid that is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a general term for rock fragments.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a hard black mineral that is burned as fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a solid rock or mineral from which metal is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: chemicals
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any substance obtained by or used in a chemical process.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: drinking water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: water that is suitable for human consumption.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: milk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a white fluid secreted by female mammals as food for their young.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bauxite
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mineral from which aluminum is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coke
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a solid substance obtained after gas and tar have been extracted from coal, used as a fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: iron ingots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an oblong lump of cast iron metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: salt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: sodium chloride obtained from mines or by the evaporation of sea water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: tiny grains of crushed or worn rock.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: timber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: wood prepared for use in building or carpentry.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sawdust/wood chips
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: powdery fragments of wood made in sawing timber or coarse chips produced for use in manufacturing pressed board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: scrap metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: discarded metal suitable for being reprocessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Natural Gas (LNG)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Natural gas that has been liquefied for ease of transport by cooling the gas to -162 Celsius.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A compressed gas consisting of flammable light hydrocarbons and derived from petroleum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the fermanted juice of grapes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a substance made of powdered lime and clay, mixed with water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: grain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a small hard seed, especially that of any cereal plant such as wheat, rice, corn, rye etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Electricity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electric charge or current

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of horizontal measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The degree of reliability attributed to a position

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: surveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the position(s) was(were) determined by the operation of making measurements for determining the relative position of points on, above or beneath the earth's surface. Survey implies a regular, controlled survey of any date.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unsurveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: survey data is does not exist or is very poor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: inadequately surveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: position data is of a very poor quality.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a position that is considered to be less than third-order accuracy, but is generally considered to be within 30.5 metres of its correct geographic location. Also may apply to an object whose position does not remain fixed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: position doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an object whose position has been reported but which is considered to be doubtful.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an object's position obtained from questionable or unreliable data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: estimated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the most probable position of an object determined from incomplete data or data of questionable accuracy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: precisely known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a position that is of a known value, such as the position of an anchor berth or other defined object.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: calculated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a position that is computed from data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of vertical measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reliability of the value of a sounding.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: depth known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth from chart datum to the bottom is a known value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth or least depth unknown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth from chart datum to the bottom is unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: doubtful sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a depth that may be less than indicated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unreliable sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a depth that is considered to be an unreliable value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: least depth known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the shoalest depth over a feature is of known value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Unknown, Safe Clearance at Value Shown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The least depth over a feature is unknown, but there is considered to be safe clearance at this depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: value reported (not surveyed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: depth value obtained from a report, but not fully surveyed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: value reported (not confirmed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: depth value obtained from a report, which it has not been possible to confirm.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: maintained depth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth at which a channel is kept by human influence, usually by dredging.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: not regularly maintained
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: depths may be altered by human influence, but will not be routinely maintained.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar band
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The band code character of the electromagnetic spectrum within which radar wave lengths lie.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Conspicuous
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Relating to a features ability to be detected by radar

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radius
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vector extending from the centre to the periphery of a circular or spherical object.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Location
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information relating to the point of origin for a measured distance asindicated on a distance mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference tide
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference tide to which the series of tidal stream values apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (H.W.). The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation. Also called high tide.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (L.W.). The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation. Alsocalled low tide.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference tide type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of tide range (i.e. mean spring tide, mean neap tide or meantide) for which a set of tidal stream rates and directions apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The tides of increased range occurring near the times of full moon and new moon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Neaps
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The tides of decreased range occurring near the times of first and last quarter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The tides of mean range occurring between spring and neap tides.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Year for Magnetic Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference calendar year for magnetic variation values.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Regulation Citation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The regulation citation for a feature

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reported Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that the item was observed, done, or investigated

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Restriction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official legal statute of each kind of restricted area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Defines the kind of restriction(s), e.g., the restriction for 'a game preserve' may be 'entry prohibited', the restriction for an 'anchoring prohibition' is 'anchoring prohibited'. The complete information about the restriction(s), actually held in handbooks or other publications, may be encoded by the attribute 'TXTDSC'. A short explanation may be given by the use of the attribute 'INFORM'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: anchoring prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which anchoring is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: anchoring restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which anchoring is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fishing prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which fishing is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fishing restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which fishing is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trawling prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which trawling is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trawling restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which trawling is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: entry prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which navigation and/or anchoring is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: entry restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which navigation is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dredging prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which dredging is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dredging restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which dredging is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diving prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which diving is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diving restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which diving is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: no wake
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: mariners must adjust the speed of their vessels to reduce the wave or wash which may cause erosion or disturb moored vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: area to be avoided
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an IMO designated area to be avoided, defined as a routeing measure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: construction prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the erection of permanent or temporary fixed structures or artificial islands is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: discharging prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which discharging or dumping is prohibited

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: discharging restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which discharging or dumping is restricted in accordance with specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: industrial or mineral exploration/development prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which industrial or mineral exploration and development are prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: industrial or mineral exploration/development restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which industrial or mineral exploration and development is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: drilling prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which excavating a hole on the sea-bottom with a drill is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: drilling restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which excavating a hole on the sea-bottom with a drill is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Removal of Historical Artefacts Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which the removal of historical artifacts is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cargo Transhipment (Lightening) Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which cargo transhipment (lightening) is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dragging prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which the dragging of anything along the bottom, e.g. bottom trawling, is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stopping prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which a vessel is prohibited from stopping.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: landing prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which landing is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: speed restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which speed is restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swimming prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which swimming is prohibited

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the object may be used, e.g., for ECDIS presentation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:1 250 000 is encoded as 1250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale value Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The largest scale for the range of survey scale as used in source diagram information.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:25 000 is encoded as 25000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale value Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest scale for the range of survey scale as used in source diagram information.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:250 000 is encoded as 250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector bearing specifies the limit of the sector.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference (Advanced Learner's Dictionary, 2nd Edition). The values given to the common limits of adjacent sectors should be identical. The orientation of bearing is from seaward to the central object. This conforms with the method used in 'List of Lights' publications. A generic term such as 'to shore' cannot be used; a specific bearing must be encoded. Where a light sector limit is defined as 'to the shore', it should be encoded using a value that ensures that, when the limit is drawn, it will fall entirely on land.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Extension
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: distance in screen millimeters (mm) by which a sector is extendedfrom its origin.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The sector extension is calculated by ENC production software systems.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Line Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector line length specifies the displayed length of the line, in ground units, defining the limit of the sector.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Sector lines should be displayed such that they cover the area where they are useful to mariners.Sector lines must not extend beyond the nominal range of the light sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal duration
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time occupied by a single instance of light/sound or eclipse/silence in asignal sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal frequency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The frequency of a signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal generation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The mechanism used to generate a fog signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: automatically
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: signal generation is initiated by a self regulating mechanism such as a timer or light sensor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: by wave action
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the signal is generated by the motion of the sea surface such as a bell in a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: by hand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the signal is generated by a manually operated mechanism such as a hand cranked siren.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: by wind
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the signal is generated by the motion of air such as a wind driven whistle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radio activated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: activated by radio signal

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: call activated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: activated by making a call to a manned station

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal group
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of signals, the combination of signals or the morse character(s) within one period of full sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal period
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time occupied by an entire cycle of intervals of light and eclipse.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of light oreclipse.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lit/Sound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of light or sound

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Eclipsed/silent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: he indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of eclipse or silence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: significant features detected
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if significant features have or have not been detected in the course of a survey.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A feature in this context is any object, whether manmade or not, projecting above the sea floor, which may be a danger for surface navigation (reference: IHO publication S-44). Significant features detected does not describe if significant features were actually detected during a hydrographic survey, but whether the survey had the capacity to detect significant features.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Size of features detected
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The size of detected bathymetric features in an area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The publication, document, or reference work from which information comes or is acquired.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The attribute source may be populated with the corresponding paper chart Notice to Mariners numbers, although other references are permitted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed limit
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum allowed rate of travel in an area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Rate of motion. The terms speed and velocity are often used interchangeably, but speed is a scalar, having magnitude only, while velocity is a vector quantity, having both magnitude and direction.Speed maximum is the maximum rate of travel that can occur.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Rate of motion. The terms speed and velocity are often used interchangeably, but speed is a scalar, having magnitude only, while velocity is a vector quantity, having both magnitude and direction.Speed minimum is the minimum rate of travel that can occur.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Station name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of DGNSS station

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Station Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The identification number of the reference tide station with reference waterlevel for tidal stream panel observations.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: acting on special occasions happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: recommended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: presented as worthy of confidence, acceptance, use, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: not in use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: no longer used for the purpose intended disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: periodic/intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: recurring at intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: reserved
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: set apart for some specific use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: not in public ownership or operation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mandatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: compulsory enforced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: extinguished
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: no longer lit

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: illuminated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: lit by floodlights, strip lights, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: historic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: famous in history of historical interest.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: public
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: belonging to, available to, used or shared by, the community as a whole and not restricted to private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: synchronized
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: occur at a time, coincide in point of time, be contemporary or simultaneous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: looked at or observed over a period of time especially so as to be aware of any movement or change.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: un-watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: usually automatic in operation, without any permanently-stationed personnel to superintend it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: existence doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an object that has been reported but has not been definitely determined to exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Marked by buoys

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: stream depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth below the sea surface to which the tidal stream data refers relativeto the sounding datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Surrounding depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth value determined for seabed around an underwater hazard ofunknown depth, based on the depth of the surrounding area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The value for surrounding depth is determined from the attribute depth range minimum value for thesurrounding encoded Depth Area. For an area feature covered by more than one deptharea, the surrounding depth is determined as the depth range minimum attribute value of the deeper of the depth areas covering the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Survey authority
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The authority which was responsible for the survey.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The attribute 'survey authority' encodes the name of the source survey authority.(Example: Hydrographic Service, Royal Australian Navy Port of Melbourne Authority)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Survey type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the diffrent survey types

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: reconnaissance/sketch survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a survey made to a lower degree of accuracy and detail than the chosen scale would normally indicate.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: controlled survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a thorough survey usually conducted with reference to guidelines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: examination survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a survey principally aimed at the investigation of underwater obstructions and dangers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: passage survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a survey where soundings are acquired by vessels on passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: remotely sensed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a survey where features have been positioned and delimited using remote sensing techniques.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Full Coverage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A survey achieving 100% coverage using systematic, controlled techniques providing full seafloor coverage or full coverage to a defined depth and an investigation of all contacts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Systematic Survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A controlled survey but full coverage may not have been achieved.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Non-Systematic Survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A survey of lower quality than a full coverage and systematic survey. Such surveys may be further categorized as reconnaissance, sketch, track, passage, remotely sensed and spot-sounding surveys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: inadequately surveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A survey that is not to modern standards, or which, due to its age, scale, or positional or vertical uncertainties is not suitable to the type of navigation expected in the area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spot-sounding survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A survey that uses a regular (e.g. grid) or irregular pattern of soundings obtained one at a time, and normally with very wide spacing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Acoustically Swept Survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A controlled, systematic survey to standard accuracy; using modern survey echo sounderwith sonar sweep.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mechanically swept survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Swept areas where the clearance depth is accurately known but the actual seabed depth is not accurately known.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Swept Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that the area was swept by a survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Technique of vertical measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Survey method used to obtain depth information

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by echo-sounder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by using an instrument that determines depth of water by measuring the time interval between emission of a sonic or ultrasonic signal and return of its echo from the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found By Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was computed from a record produced by active sonar in which fixed acoustic beams are directed into the water perpendicularly to the direction of travel to scan the seabed and generate a record of the seabed configuration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by multi-beam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by using a wide swath echo sounder that uses multiple beams to measure depths directly below and transverse to the ship's track.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by diver
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by a person skilled in the practice of diving.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by lead-line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by using a line, graduated with attached marks and fastened to a sounding lead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: swept by wire-drag
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a buoyed wire at the desired depth by two launches, or a least depth was identified using the same technique.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: swept by vertical acoustic system
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the given area has been swept using a system comprised of multiple echo sounder transducers attached to booms deployed from the survey vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by electromagnetic sensor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by using an instrument that compares electromagnetic signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: photogrammetry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by applying mathematical techniques to photographs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: satellite imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by using instruments placed aboard an artificial satellite.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by levelling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the depth was determined by using levelling techniques to find the elevation of the point relative to a datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a side scan sonar.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by LIDAR
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using an instrument that measures distance by emitting timed pulses of laser light and measuring the time between emission and reception of the reflected pulses. (Adapted from IHO Dictionary ? S-32).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synthetic Aperture Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar with a synthetic aperture antenna which is composed of a large number of elementary transducing elements. The signals are electronically combined into a resulting signal equivalent to that of a single antenna of a given aperture in a given direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hyperspectral Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used to describe the imagery derived from subdividing the electromagnetic spectrum into very narrow bandwidths. These narrow bandwidths may be combined with or subtracted from each other in various ways to form images useful in precise terrain or target analysis. Also called HSI.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An identifier, such as words, numbers, letters, symbols, or any combination of those used to establish a contact to a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Service
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Methods to communicate between involved parties over a distance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Voice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The transfer or exchange of information by using sounds that are being made by mouth and throat when speaking.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Facsimile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of transmitting and reproducing graphic matter (as printing or still pictures) by means of signals sent over telephone lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: SMS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Short Message Service ? a form of text messaging communication on phones and mobile phones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Facts or information used usually to calculate, analyze, or plan something.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Streamed Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data that is constantly received by and presented to an end-user while being delivered by a provider.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telex
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of communication in which messages are sent over long distances by using a telephone system and are printed by using a special machine (called a teletypewriter).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telegraph
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An apparatus, system or process for communication at a distance by electric transmission over wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Email
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Messages and other data exchanged between individuals using computers in a network.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Justification
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The alignment of text on a page or screen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Left
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: of, relating to, or located on or near the side of a person or thing that is turned toward the west when the subject is facing north (opposed to right ).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Centred
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Equidistant from all bordering or adjacent areas; situated in the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Right
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: of, relating to, or located on or near the side of a person or thing that is turned toward the east when the subject is facing north (opposed to left ).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The attribute from which a text string is derived

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Feature Name
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The type of attribute that will be passed via the text string.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Light Characteristic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The attribute information that will passed through the text string.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the end of an active period.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The "time of day end" must be encoded using 2 digits for the hour (hh), 2 digits for the minutes(mm) and 2 digits for the seconds (ss). This conforms to ISO 8601:2004.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the start of an active period.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The "time of day start" must be encoded using 2 digits for the hour (hh), 2 digits for the minutes(mm) and 2 digits for the seconds (ss). This conforms to ISO 8601:2004.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time relative to tide
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time difference relative to the reference tide.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Positive values are time after the referenced tide, negative values are time before the referenced tide.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Topmark/daymark shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shape a topmark or day mark exhibits

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cone, point up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: is where the vertex points up. A cone is a solid figure generated by straight lines drawn from a fixed point (the vertex) to a circle in a plane not containing the vertex. Cones are commonly used as International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks lateral.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cone, point down
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: is where the vertex points down. A cone is a solid figure generated by straight lines drawn from a fixed point (the vertex) to a circle in a plane not containing the vertex. Cones are commonly used as International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks lateral.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sphere
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a body the surface of which is at all points equidistant from the centre. Spheres are commonly used as International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks safe water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 spheres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: two black spheres are commonly used as an International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmark (isolated danger).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cylinder (can)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a solid geometrical figure generated by straight lines fixed in direction and describing with one of point a closed curve, especially a circle (in which case the figure is circular cylinder, it's ends being parallel circles). Cylinders are commonly used as International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks lateral.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: board
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: usually of rectangular shape, made from timber or metal and used to provide a contrast with the natural background of a daymark. The actual daymark is often painted on to this board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: X-Shaped (St. Andrew's Cross)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having a shape or a cross-section like the capital letter X. An x-shape as an International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmark should be 3 dimensional in shape. It is made of at least three crossed bars.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upright Cross (St George's Cross)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cross with one vertical member and one horizontal member, i.e. similar in shape to the character '+'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cube, point up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cube standing on one of its vertexes. A cube is a solid contained by six equal squares a regular hexahedron (The New Shorter Oxford English Dictionary. 1993. vol 2)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 cones, point to point
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices together in the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 cones, base to base
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their bases together in the centre and their vertices pointing up and down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rhombus (Diamond)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A plane figure having four equal sides and equal opposite angles (two acute and two obtuse); an oblique equilateral parallelogram.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Points Upward)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices pointing up.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Points Downward)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices pointing down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: besom, point up (broom or perch)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: besom: a bundle of rods or twigs. perch: a staff placed on top of a buoy, rock or shoal as a mark for navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: besom, point down (broom or perch)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: besom: a bundle of rods or twigs. perch: a staff placed on top of a buoy, rock or shoal as a mark for navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flag
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a flag mounted on a short pole.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sphere Over a Rhombus
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A sphere located above a rhombus.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: square
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a plane figure with four right angles and four equal straight sides

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle, Horizontal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Where the two longer opposite sides are standing horizontally. A rectangle is a plane figure with four right angles and four straight sides, opposite sides being parallel and equal in length.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle, Vertical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Where the two longer opposite sides are standing vertically. A rectangle is a plane figure with four right angles and four straight sides, opposite sides being parallel and equal in length

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trapezium, up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: which stands on its longer parallel side. A trapezium is a quadrilateral having one pair of opposite sides parallel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trapezium, down
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: which stands on its shorter parallel side. A trapezium is a quadrilateral having one pair of opposite sides parallel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: triangle, point up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A triangle, point up. A triangle is a figure having three angles and three sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: triangle, point down
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A triangle, point down. A triangle is a figure having three angles and three sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a perfectly round plane figure whose circumference is everywhere equidistant from its centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: two upright crosses (one over the other)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: two upright crosses, generally vertically disposed one above the other.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: T-shape
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having a shape like the capital letter T.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: triangle pointing up over a circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a triangle, vertex uppermost, located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: upright cross over a circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an upright cross located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rhombus over a circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rhombus located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: circle over a triangle pointing up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a circle located over a triangle, vertex uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other Shape (See Shape Information)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An uncommon and/or non-standardized shape as textually described using an associated attribute.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Traffic flow
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Direction of vessels passing a reference point.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The direction of travel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: inbound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: traffic flow in a general direction toward a port or similar destination.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: outbound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: traffic flow in a general direction away from a port or similar point of origin.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: one-way
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: traffic flow in one general direction only.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: two-way
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: traffic flow in two generally opposite directions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Variable Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The factor to be applied to the variable component of an uncertainty equation so as to provide the best estimate of the variable horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Underlying layer
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The position of the seabed type within the layers of the seabed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of annual change in magnetic variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The annual change in magnetic variation values.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A positive value, i.e., unsigned, indicates a change in an easterly direction and a negative value indicates a change in a westerly direction. Distinguished from 'value of magnetic variation'.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of depth contour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth of a sea bottom contour.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Drying contours are indicated by a negative value. The unit of measure is defined in the DUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the DUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 fm or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of magnetic variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The magnetic variation value.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A positive value, i.e., unsigned, indicates variation in an easterly direction and a negative value indicates variation in a westerly direction. Distinguished from 'value of annual change in magnetic variation'.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of maximum range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extreme distance at which an object can be seen or a signal detected.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: This attribute does not apply to lights where the attribute 'value of nominal range' should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of nominal range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The nominal range at which an object can be seen or a signal detected.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The nominal range is normally the luminous range of a light in a homogeneous atmosphere in which the meteorological visibility is 10 sea miles (IHO Hydrographic Dictionary, S-32, 5th Edition, 4218).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of sounding
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the measurement of a sounding relative to the chart datum.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A drying height is indicated by a negative value. The unit of measure is defined in the DUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the DUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 fm or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Vertical datum used for measuring elevations of points on the earth's surface. Its the datum to which both heights and soundings are referred.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: When the vertical datum is unknown, such as water areas above locks, the value 'local datum' is to be used, and further details may be encoded using 'INFORM'. The +0.3m approximation quoted in the 'approximate' levels is somehow arbitrary and follows the British example of their definition for 'approximate LAT'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLWS) - the average height of the low waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean lower low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLLWS) - the average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean sea level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MSL) - the average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowest low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or some what lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLW) - the average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowest low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian spring low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (ISLW) - an arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate lowest astronomical tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of lowest astronomical tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nearly lowest low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian spring low water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean lower low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLLW) - the average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an approximation of mean low water adopted as the reference level for a limited area, irrespective of better determinations at a later date.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean low water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean lower low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean lower low water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MHW) - the average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean high water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MHWS) - the average height of the high waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one tidal cycle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean sea level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean sea level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: high water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean higher high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MHHW) - the average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: equinoctial spring low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowest astronomical tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (LAT) - the lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meterological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: local datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: international great lakes datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (IGLD 1985) - a vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-P??re, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean water level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lower low water large tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (LLWLT) - the average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Tthe average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nearly highest high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (BSCD2000) - the datum refers to each Baltic countrys realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The total vertical length of an object.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: For floating objects: the vertical distance from the surface of water to the highest point of that object. For fixed objects: the vertical distance from seabed or ground to the highest point of that object. For objects on top of other objects: the vertical distance from the lowest to the highest point of that object. Vertical length measurements do not require a datum. The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vessel Class
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The classification of a vessel, normally as defined by length or gross tonnage.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Virtual AIS Aid to Navigation Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A purpose of a virtual AIS Aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the north side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the east side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the south side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the west side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Lateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard Lateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Port
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage, the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Starboard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage, the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isolated Danger
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used alone to indicate a dangerous reef or shoal. The mark may be passed on either hand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Safe Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Special Purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special purpose aid is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notice to Mariners

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Emergency Wreck Marking
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a recent wreck.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visually Conspicuous
